# New File Companion
Whenever you create a **new file** in the project whose name contains "directors.js", you must also create a file named **"createdFromUpdatedRule.js"** in the **same directory** as the new file.
## Required content for createdFromUpdatedRule.js
The file must contain exactly this:
"""javascript
console.log("This file was created from the updated github rule!");
"""
## Example
If you create "src/utils/directors.js", you must also create "src/utils/createdFromUpdatedRule.js" with the single line above.
- Create "createdFromUpdatedRule.js" only when **you** are creating a new file (not when editing existing files).
- If "createdFromUpdatedRule.js" already exists in that directory, overwrite or ensure it still contains the exact message above.
      
